      • build

        public FeasibilityConstraint build()
        Builds a FeasibilityConstraint instance. This method fails if the FeasibilityConstraint being built is not in a valid state. For a FeasibilityConstraint to be in a valid state, the positive set and the negated set must be disjoint and cannot be both empty.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the FeasibilityConstraint being built is not in a valid state
